        <div type="letter">
            <div type="text">
                <opener>
                    <placeName><hi rend="print">Down. | Bromley. | Kent. S.E.</hi></placeName>
                    <salute>My dear Sir</salute>
                </opener>
                <div type="transcription">
                     
<p>M. Ch. Phipps Haussoullier of 52 Grand Rue des Batignolles, Paris, has applied to me for authorization for translating into French my Naturalist’s Voyage.<ref target="#foot.f2"/> I should be <hi rend="underline">very</hi> glad of this. As you have copyright, will be so kind as to grant permission, &amp; if so, please to send me the proper authorization that I may forward it to him— I hope that you will not object, &amp; believe me yours very sincerely | Ch. Darwin</p>
<p>P.S. How has this Book sold since you printed an Edit. uniform with Origin?<ref target="#foot.f3"/></p> 
                </div>
            </div>
            <div type="tnotes">
                <note xml:id="tnote.n1">1.2 I] <hi rend="italic">over illeg</hi> </note>
            </div>

            
            
            
            
            
            
        </div>

        

        

        <div type="footnotes">
            <note xml:id="foot.f1">The date is established by the relationship between this letter, the <ref target="./DCP-LETT-6586.xml" resp="#automat">letter from C. P. Haussoullier, 31 January 1869</ref>, and the <ref target="./DCP-LETT-6597.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">letter from John Murray, 3 February [1869]</ref>.</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f2">CD refers to <ref target="../nameregs/nameregs_2167.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">Charles Phipps Haussoullier</ref> and to <ref target="../bibliographies/bibl_4250.xml" resp="#mjhawkins"><hi rend="italic">Journal of researches</hi></ref> (see <ref target="./DCP-LETT-6586.xml" resp="#automat">letter from C. P. Haussoullier, 31 January 1869</ref> and n. 1).</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f3">CD refers to <ref target="../bibliographies/bibl_4254.xml" resp="#mjhawkins"><hi rend="italic">Journal of researches</hi> (1860)</ref>. For more on the publishing history of the book, including changes to the title and appearance of different editions, see <ref target="../bibliographies/bibl_2661.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">Freeman 1977</ref>.</note>
        </div>        
            
